stand how to approach projects where the full requirements are not known at the outset; Gives advice on how to combine the benefits of Agile and waterfall project management methodologies for successful project implementation; Helps readers take a thorough approach to risk management; and Provides a universal approach to project management, making sure that it is accessible for multiple industries and not wedded to software development practices. Project managers, IT managers, consultants and other senior managers trying to develop a project management approach suitable for their organisation, or those employees expected to take on project management or ‘client/product owner’ roles without any briefing or other support will find this book extremely valuable. It will also benefit any readers doing a project assurance review for the first time, as well as Agile users who want to know how to fill the gaps in their current method, such as quality and risk management. Buy this book today for a universal and successful approach to project management!  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aAgile project management. 0aElectronic books. 0aProject managementxMethodology. 0aProject management. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Project Management.2bisacsh  aAgile.  aManagement.  aPM4A.  aProject Management for All.  aProject Management.  aScrum.  aWaterfall Project Management.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSciendo All Ebooks Trial Collection 2024z97831115024960 cEPUBz978178778233440uhttps://sciendo.com/book/9781787782327  a978-3-11-150249-6  Sciendo All Ebooks Trial Collection 2024b2024  aGBV-deGruyter-alles